{quote}*Requested by:*   Anne at Gmbh
*Requested for:*  Surgeon App (iOS/Android) & Virtual Surgery

*Summary*

 Remove translated text for Polish and German and use only English text

Concern expressed from Gmbh legal team that users of the app would get the impression that the app was owned by Gmbh

Updated 2/2 - Per Anne, we will update the Terms & Conditions which displays the first time the user logs into Surgeon App to English as well.  We have also expanded this to include French.  

*Action Items*

Waiting for answer regarding the links to translated privacy policy and legal and ethics notice available during account creation.

*Correspondence*

Hi Eve,

there is a German translation of the privacy policy (under „Settings“) in the Surgeon App (see also screenshot attached). And the same in Polish.

Our legal department remarked that having this text translated into these languages could be misleading in that it would make people think this were an app owned GmbH.

So could you please replace the current German and Polish versions with the English one? We will not have this translated into French.

Thank you
Anne 

*Update from Anne -- Note this will only be for iOS as Android and VS use* [*A.com*|http://A.com] *to create user accounts*

Hi Eve,

our legal department said it would be ideal if these links could also direct to the English sites with the privacy policy and legal and ethics notice of Arthrex Inc.

Thank you
Anne{quote}

fields.summary: DEV: Investigate Playbook Worker Updates Not seen in App

comments.body:
The team found several possible bugs that could have contributed to the disappearing playbooks:

* *invalid data in Kontent* 
** specifically any custom links (within a Compact or Regular Link) that were not filled out but instead had the link type = default were causing the playbooks to not be built but also we’re not properly throwing an Error Component in the Playbook 
* versioning is not yet supported
** if a playbook is published and a user creates a new version → the worker does not yet handle this, we will create a ticket for setting up composite ids to handle the draft and published versioning
Created [https://arthrex.atlassian.net/browse/AMOBS-477|https://arthrex.atlassian.net/browse/AMOBS-477|smart-link]  after this investigation

Separate tickets will be setup to implement composite playbook ids so we can handle versioning of Playbooks. 
\{id}-draft
\{id}-published
